📌 TODO API with FastAPI

A simple Task Management REST API built using FastAPI
.
This project demonstrates how to create a beginner-friendly API with CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for managing TODO tasks.

🚀 Features

✅ Create a new task

📖 Get all tasks or a single task by ID

✏️ Update existing tasks

❌ Delete tasks

🏠 Root route with welcome message

⚡ Built with FastAPI for speed and simplicity

Requirements-
1)Python 3.8+
2)FastAPI
3)Uvicorn (ASGI server)
4)Pydantic

After executing the API can run on-
Server will run on: http://127.0.0.1:8000
Interactive API Docs: http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
Alternative API Docs: http://127.0.0.1:8000/redoc

Future Improvements
Store tasks in a real database (SQLite/PostgreSQL) instead of in-memory list,
Add authentication (JWT tokens),
Add filtering and pagination,
Deploy to cloud (Heroku, Render, AWS, etc.).
